other_tests.findings: Normal chromosome karyotype; chromosomal microarray analysis revealed a heterozygous deletion of 23.9 Mb in the chromosome 5q11.1-q21.3 region of the fetus, variant of uncertain significance (VUS).

other_tests.procedure_name: Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the fetal brain
other_tests.findings: Cystic structures around the bilateral lateral ventricles and abnormal signal foci in the white matter of the right parietal lobe. Smaller diameters and sulci compared to normal fetuses.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Follow-up MRI at 28+1 weeks showed mild dilation of the bilateral ventricles, increased size of cystic structures, and continued abnormal signal foci in the white matter of the fetal right parietal lobe, along with a decrease in overall brain size.

other_tests.findings: The fetus carried the TREX1:NM_033629.6:exon2:c.294dup:p.C99Mfs*3 homozygous variant. Both parents were heterozygous carriers of this mutation.
